- Apply `authenticateToken` as route-level middleware on POST, PUT, DELETE
- POST: derive `userId` from `req.user!.userId` (ignore body's userId)
- PUT: after finding post, check `post.userId !== req.user!.userId` → 403
- DELETE: after finding post, check `post.userId !== req.user!.userId` → 403

Key changes per route:
```
POST /posts      → router.post("/", authenticateToken, handler)
                   newPost.userId = req.user!.userId  (not from body)

PUT /posts/:id   → router.put("/:id", authenticateToken, handler)
                   if (posts[index].userId !== req.user!.userId) → 403

DELETE /posts/:id → router.delete("/:id", authenticateToken, handler)
                    if (posts[index].userId !== req.user!.userId) → 403
```

GET routes remain unchanged (no auth).

### 5. `src/routes/comments.ts`

- Import `authenticateToken` from `../middleware/auth.js`
- Apply `authenticateToken` on POST (new comment), PUT (update), DELETE
- POST: derive `userId` from `req.user!.userId`
