The seed users (alice, bob, charlie) have **plaintext** passwords in `db.ts`. After this change, the login endpoint will compare `hashPassword(inputPassword)` against the stored value. Since the stored values are not hashed, seed users cannot log in via the API — but **no existing test relies on logging in as a seed user**. All auth tests register fresh users. All existing `posts.test.ts` and `comments.test.ts` tests use GET-only public endpoints. No changes to `db.ts` are needed.

---

